Vielen Dank vom ganzen Wheelmap-Team!

Beste Grüße,
Andi




English version: Reconnect Wheelmap account with OpenStreetMap
==============================================================

Dear Wheelmapper,

we beaver away feverishly on the simplification of the Wheelmap registration process. Therefore, with this email we kindly ask you to reconnect your Wheelmap account with OpenStreetMap until June 30th.

In our blog post we have outlined for you how to dis- and reconnect: http://blog.wheelmap.org/en/participate/how-to-disconnect-and-sign-up-again/
Click here to go to your accout directly: <%= @url %>

Background:
About 250.000 places have been tagged during the last one and a half years on Wheelmap. Many thanks! In order to further improve our online map for the future we want to advance the registration process.

By reconnecting again you grant us the following two rights which we need in future:
- to read your user settings (We read out the OSM-ID anonymously in order to be able to assign your tags.)
- to make entries into the OpenStreetMap database (OSM)

With these new rights we are able ensure that there will be fewer login problems during the development of Wheelmap.

If you use Wheelmap on your iPhone, it is absolutely necessary to reconnect. Only this enables you to keep using your email + password on your iPhone in order to tag places.
If something doesn’t work or if any issues arise, please contact me.
It’d be great if you make these changes until July 15th, since we’d like to change the registration process for all users hereafter.

Many thanks from the Wheelmap!

Best wishes,
Andi